want to know?

262
00:12:22,273 --> 00:12:24,818
Oh thank you! I'll tell
you every detail...!

263
00:12:24,901 --> 00:12:26,486
It's the most heart-wrenching,

264
00:12:26,569 --> 00:12:30,573
tear-jerking story of lost
love you'll ever hear!

265
00:12:32,283 --> 00:12:33,702
This very park
is the place

266
00:12:33,785 --> 00:12:36,413
where I first set
my eyes on him.

267
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,250
Excuse me Miss.

268
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:41,876
yes?

269
00:12:44,963 --> 00:12:46,965
Fate brought us
together that day.

270
00:12:48,591 --> 00:12:49,759
Over some leeks?

271
00:12:49,843 --> 00:12:51,177
C'mon...

272
00:12:51,261 --> 00:12:52,595
This sounds like the plot
for some lame old

273
00:12:52,679 --> 00:12:54,389
black and white movie.

274
00:12:54,472 --> 00:12:55,849
We would often meet
here at the park

275
00:12:55,932 --> 00:12:58,184
for the most romantic dates...

276
00:12:58,268 --> 00:12:59,978
Everyone around us
would get so jealous

277
00:13:00,061 --> 00:13:01,271
over how close
we had become.

278
00:13:02,522 --> 00:13:04,065
BUT THEN!

279
00:13:04,149 --> 00:13:05,650
He...

280
00:13:05,734 --> 00:13:07,318
He!

281
00:13:15,994 --> 00:13:16,953
How about we catch
a movie sometime?

282
00:13:20,665 --> 00:13:22,500
No, it can't be.

283
00:13:25,837 --> 00:13:27,756
So that jerk was
two timing you...?

284
00:13:27,839 --> 00:13:29,132
What a piece of garbage.

285
00:13:29,215 --> 00:13:30,550
Yes it's true!

286
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:32,344
I loved this park
before I met him

287
00:13:32,427 --> 00:13:35,096
and now it only brings
up bad memories!

288
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:36,890
What's your reason
behind using water?

289
00:13:38,516 --> 00:13:40,435
Tell me! Who is this woman?

290
00:13:40,518 --> 00:13:42,479
I deserve an answer
now say something!

291
00:13:42,562 --> 00:13:44,105
Get lost will ya?

292
00:13:47,609 --> 00:13:50,153
Can't you see You're
bothering my lady friend.

293
00:13:50,236 --> 00:13:52,113
This guy must be the
scum of the earth!

294
00:13:52,197 --> 00:13:54,366
you can say that again.

295
00:13:54,449 --> 00:13:58,036
I was so lonely and
depressed over this guy,

296
00:13:58,119 --> 00:14:00,330
I decided to end
it all right here,

297
00:14:00,413 --> 00:14:02,207
in these gorgeous
gardens that once held

298
00:14:02,290 --> 00:14:04,834
only my most
beautiful memories.

299
00:14:04,918 --> 00:14:06,419
Y'mean suicide?

300
00:14:06,503 --> 00:14:08,004
Yes...

301
00:14:08,088 --> 00:14:09,464
I do

302
00:14:28,316 --> 00:14:30,151
Hey Lady! What do you
think you're doing?

303
00:14:34,030 --> 00:14:35,448
Nooo!

304
00:14:35,532 --> 00:14:37,409
I failed every time,

305
00:14:37,492 --> 00:14:39,911
but once I gave up and
starting walking home...

306
00:14:57,178 --> 00:14:59,222
That was almost
six months ago.

307
00:14:59,305 --> 00:15:01,474
Which is when the first
occurrence happened.

308
00:15:01,558 --> 00:15:04,477
And now I'm stuck
in this awful limbo.

309
00:15:04,561 --> 00:15:06,354
So why don't you just
like go up to this guy

310
00:15:06,438 --> 00:15:07,981
and haunt him directly?

311
00:15:08,064 --> 00:15:10,150
Now Mai that wouldn't
be a very good idea.

312
00:15:10,233 --> 00:15:12,277
It sounds to me like this
creep needs to have

313
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,154
a scare or two put in him.

314
00:15:14,237 --> 00:15:16,990
That's what I thought,
and I did try that.

315
00:15:17,073 --> 00:15:17,949
But...

316
00:15:19,868 --> 00:15:22,746
I curse you!

317
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,793
I can't believe how
much we are alike.

318
00:15:28,877 --> 00:15:31,379
It's like I've finally met
my soulmate or something.

319
00:15:35,425 --> 00:15:37,635
again I was a
total failure!

320
00:15:37,719 --> 00:15:40,013
This guy seems
pretty insensitive.

321
00:15:40,096 --> 00:15:42,557
I couldn't bear going
through this pain alone.

322
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:44,684
So I decided to haunt
all the couples

323
00:15:44,768 --> 00:15:47,270
that came here and let
them know how I feel!

324
00:15:49,814 --> 00:15:52,150
-Damn it!
-Was that really necessary?

325
00:15:53,568 --> 00:15:55,236
Serves you right!

326
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,821
Stop it!

327
00:15:56,905 --> 00:15:57,906
Attacking random people

328
00:15:57,989 --> 00:15:59,657
just because you're
mad at some jerk

329
00:15:59,741 --> 00:16:02,327
is just gonna make
everyone mad at you.

330
00:16:02,410 --> 00:16:03,703
Is that what you want?

331
00:16:03,787 --> 00:16:04,704
What's with you Mai?

332
00:16:04,788 --> 00:16:06,414
Why are you so worked up?

333
00:16:06,498 --> 00:16:07,665
Well I...

334
00:16:14,839 --> 00:16:17,050
I just can't
stand grudges...

335
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:19,302
Life is too short.

336
00:16:22,263 --> 00:16:23,306
You know she's right.

337
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:24,599
If you keep this
up you'll become

338
00:16:24,683 --> 00:16:26,643
what's known as a
sitebound spirit.

339
00:16:26,726 --> 00:16:28,103
Trust us. You'd
be much happier

340
00:16:28,186 --> 00:16:30,105
crossing over now than
trying to get even.

341
00:16:30,188 --> 00:16:31,523
If you'd like to do that,

342
00:16:31,606 --> 00:16:33,024
there's still time.

343
00:16:33,108 --> 00:16:36,569
Are you all in some
nerdy ghost club?

344
00:16:36,653 --> 00:16:38,029
Well Not exactly.

345
00:16:38,113 --> 00:16:39,489
So what do you think?

346
00:16:39,572 --> 00:16:40,949
I would have to imagine
that living in limbo

347
00:16:41,032 --> 00:16:43,827
like this gets
old after awhile.

348
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:46,413
Maybe it is
time I moved on.

349
00:16:46,496 --> 00:16:48,081
Wait!

350
00:16:48,164 --> 00:16:49,457
Even though I don't believe
in holding a grudge,

351
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:51,668
crossing over now wouldn't
deal with the problem.

352
00:16:51,751 --> 00:16:54,129
You would only be
sweeping it under the rug.

353
00:16:55,505 --> 00:16:56,881
Well... I mean is it's
not fair for the guy

354
00:16:56,965 --> 00:16:58,299
to get away with it...

355
00:16:58,383 --> 00:17:00,468
And I think you
deserve some closure.

356
00:17:00,552 --> 00:17:01,678
You shouldn't worry.

357
00:17:01,761 --> 00:17:03,054
What goes around
comes around.

358
00:17:03,138 --> 00:17:05,015
He'll get his just
desserts alright.

359
00:17:05,098 --> 00:17:06,725
If she's content
with letting it go

360
00:17:06,808 --> 00:17:08,393
then we shouldn't pry.

361
00:17:08,476 --> 00:17:10,478
It's all up to you.

362
00:17:14,566 --> 00:17:16,067
It's him.

363
00:17:21,489 --> 00:17:22,699
I want to teach that
dirtbag a lesson

364
00:17:22,782 --> 00:17:25,035
he'll never forget.

365
00:17:25,118 --> 00:17:26,327
But you've already
tried that before

366
00:17:26,411 --> 00:17:27,495
and it never worked.

367
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:30,540
How will this be
any different?

368
00:17:30,623 --> 00:17:32,625
I have an idea.

369
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,593
Excuse me.

370
00:17:41,676 --> 00:17:43,511
You recently did
something extremely cruel

371
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:46,306
to someone who cared
about you very much.

372
00:17:46,389 --> 00:17:49,517
I sense an evil aura
surrounding him.

373
00:17:49,601 --> 00:17:50,894
I can see it...

374
00:17:50,977 --> 00:17:53,688
The spirit of a woman who
was led to suicide by you.

375
00:17:53,772 --> 00:17:55,231
Who are you people?

376
00:17:55,315 --> 00:17:57,025
I don't know what the
hell you're talking about!

377
00:17:57,108 --> 00:17:59,235
You practically
killed her.

378
00:17:59,319 --> 00:18:02,280
Its said a woman's curse
lasts a hundred generations.

379
00:18:02,364 --> 00:18:05,367
You should have her
exorcised as soon as possible.

380
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:06,951
You must have me mistaken
for someone else.

381
00:18:07,035 --> 00:18:09,079
I mean why would I
need an exorcism?

382
00:18:10,538 --> 00:18:13,833
hey, you're ...
You're from TV.

383
00:18:16,086 --> 00:18:17,504
Hey... Stop...!

384
00:18:17,587 --> 00:18:19,381
What the hell?

385
00:18:21,716 --> 00:18:23,218
It's... It's you.

386
00:18:30,016 --> 00:18:33,061
How does it feel to be on the
other end of your torment?

387
00:18:36,147 --> 00:18:38,191
Spare me, please!

388
00:18:38,274 --> 00:18:39,984
I didn't mean to hurt
anyone! I swear!

389
00:18:43,988 --> 00:18:45,782
Oh I feel so
much better...

390
00:18:45,865 --> 00:18:48,660
Now I can cross over
without any regrets.

391
00:18:48,743 --> 00:18:50,662
Thank you so much.

392
00:18:58,336 --> 00:19:01,965
And with that, the
woman's spirit was purified.

393
00:19:06,469 --> 00:19:07,971
Mai you were
awesome today.

394
00:19:09,597 --> 00:19:11,599
And let's not forget the
hilarious performance

395
00:19:11,683 --> 00:19:13,101
Masako put on.

396
00:19:13,184 --> 00:19:14,561
What did I do?

397
00:19:14,644 --> 00:19:17,689
You went up to Naru and
started hugging and cuddling!

398
00:19:17,772 --> 00:19:20,066
And then you topped it
off with a big kiss.

399
00:19:21,109 --> 00:19:23,111
I kissed him? Seriously?

400
00:19:23,194 --> 00:19:26,197
Not just once, but
like a dozen times!

401
00:19:26,281 --> 00:19:27,490
No she didn't!

402
00:19:27,574 --> 00:19:30,076
why would you lie to
her face like that?

403
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,579
Wait a minute! You
guys are lying to me?

404
00:19:32,662 --> 00:19:35,415
Well you did hug him
and paw him for awhile.

405
00:19:35,498 --> 00:19:38,710
But I didn't kiss him.
Is that right?

406
00:19:38,793 --> 00:19:40,378
I would never
let you kiss him.

407
00:19:40,462 --> 00:19:42,255
Never in a million years!

408
00:19:42,339 --> 00:19:44,966
Just you wait Masako,
next time I won't eve-...

409
00:19:46,509 --> 00:19:49,137
You're all still here...? Is
there nothing better to do?

410
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:51,139
We just love being
in your presence...

411
00:19:51,222 --> 00:19:52,682
and must we remind you
why you finished

412
00:19:52,766 --> 00:19:54,642
your investigation early?

413
00:19:54,726 --> 00:19:56,728
Although I do truly
appreciate your help

414
00:19:56,811 --> 00:19:57,812
in the investigation,

415
00:19:57,896 --> 00:19:58,980
I never would
have imagined

416
00:19:59,064 --> 00:20:00,774
that you would have
so much free time

417
00:20:00,857 --> 00:20:03,318
that you'd start just hanging
out here after work.

418
00:20:03,401 --> 00:20:05,445
Are you saying that
I have no life!

419
00:20:05,528 --> 00:20:06,613
You're the one who practically
lives at his office!

420
00:20:06,696 --> 00:20:08,406
Naru I'd like to buy
you some dinner

421
00:20:08,490 --> 00:20:11,159
to thank you for all the help
you've given me today.

422
00:20:11,242 --> 00:20:12,494
Oh please!

423
00:20:12,577 --> 00:20:14,871
Naru would never fall for
such an obvious come on.

424
00:20:14,954 --> 00:20:16,289
That sounds nice.

425
00:20:16,373 --> 00:20:18,083
What...? You're going? !

426
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:20,335
Of course he is.

427
00:20:20,418 --> 00:20:22,837
This isn't the first time
we've gone out together Mai.

428
00:20:22,921 --> 00:20:24,839
just last week
we saw a movie...

429
00:20:24,923 --> 00:20:26,508
Let's go Naru.

430
00:20:28,551 --> 00:20:30,804
Naru, you idiot!

431
00:20:30,887 --> 00:20:32,847
Why didn't you tell her to
get lost like you always do?

432
00:20:34,057 --> 00:20:35,225
Ayako may be right.

433
00:20:35,308 --> 00:20:37,060
I think she is
blackmailing him.

434
00:20:37,143 --> 00:20:39,229
I always just assumed
they had a patron together.

435
00:20:39,312 --> 00:20:41,106
Patron? !!

436
00:20:41,189 --> 00:20:43,566
Actually, it's quite common
in the US and Europe.

437
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:46,319
Parapsychology isn't a
recognized field of science yet,

438
00:20:46,403 --> 00:20:48,113
so all research
labs like Naru's

439
00:20:48,196 --> 00:20:49,989
need some type of
financial support.

440
00:20:50,073 --> 00:20:51,825
They'll often find
private sponsors

441
00:20:51,908 --> 00:20:53,868
or even large corporations
to help with funding.

442
00:20:55,412 --> 00:20:57,205
Oh so that's
what you meant.

443
00:20:57,288 --> 00:20:58,915
You had me worried there.

444
00:20:58,998 --> 00:21:00,375
Why?

445
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:02,794
Well in Japan the word
patron has another meaning,

446
00:21:02,877 --> 00:21:04,921
having to do with
the subject of geishas

447
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:06,256
Ohh.

448
00:21:06,339 --> 00:21:08,550
Yeah ... file that away
for future reference...

449
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:09,801
Though you may be right.

450
00:21:09,884 --> 00:21:12,262
If he has a sponsor it
could be Masako's dad.

451
00:21:12,345 --> 00:21:14,681
Then he may feel
obligated to date Masako...

452
00:21:14,764 --> 00:21:16,266
Huh.

453
00:21:16,349 --> 00:21:17,726
For him to afford the
rent on a place like this

454
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:19,477
he must have a sponsor.

455
00:21:19,561 --> 00:21:21,563
Is it that
expensive here?

456
00:21:21,646 --> 00:21:22,981
It's not just the rent.

457
00:21:23,064 --> 00:21:25,483
You have to factor in the
cost of all this equipment.

458
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:26,901
Have you ever looked
at the price tag

459
00:21:26,985 --> 00:21:28,903
of one of those high-speed
cameras he owns?

460
00:21:28,987 --> 00:21:30,238
I don't want to know.

461
00:21:38,246 --> 00:21:41,166
It must be nice to
have a date with Naru.

462
00:21:41,249 --> 00:21:42,584
hey Mai...

463
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:44,878
You wanna go catch
a movie with me?

464
00:21:44,961 --> 00:21:46,546
I guess so.

465
00:21:46,629 --> 00:21:48,381
Then we have a date...

466
00:21:48,465 --> 00:21:51,634
Later we'll grab some food.
Anything you want... 'huh?

467
00:21:51,718 --> 00:21:53,970
Aww Monk. That's so sweet!

468
00:21:54,054 --> 00:21:55,805
He's trying to
cheer me up.

469
00:21:55,889 --> 00:21:57,807
I love you Monk!

470
00:21:57,891 --> 00:21:58,933
That sounds like
a great time!

471
00:21:59,017 --> 00:22:00,810
You've got your
own Lolita now.

472
00:22:00,894 --> 00:22:02,520
It's better than having
a date with my couch

473
00:22:02,604 --> 00:22:03,855
like someone I know

474
00:22:03,938 --> 00:22:05,106
Oh aren't you cute.

475
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:06,358
I actually do have a date.

476
00:22:06,441 --> 00:22:08,234
But I think Lin's
working late tonight

477
00:22:08,318 --> 00:22:09,986
Oh It's not him.

478
00:22:13,490 --> 00:22:14,991
She means me?

479
00:22:15,075 --> 00:22:16,868
Don't worry John.
I'll play nice.

480
00:22:16,951 --> 00:22:18,536
Be careful John.

481
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:20,497
She may try to stick
you with the bill.

482
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:21,873
What a crazy day...!

483
00:22:21,956 --> 00:22:23,958
Lin. You mind closing
up for the night?

484
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:40,183
[Music]

485
00:22:40,266 --> 00:22:50,193
[Music]

486
00:23:59,804 --> 00:24:00,930
Next time on Ghost Hunt.

487
00:24:01,014 --> 00:24:02,974
Silent Christmas, Part One!

488
00:24:03,058 --> 00:24:04,893
I love the holidays!

